---+ OSG Software Team Meeting for 16-Jan-2011

January 16th was Martin Luther King Jr. Day, so the meeting was not held. Instead we collected status reports by email, which are below. 

---++ Update to OSG 1.2.26

We need to do a security release for the Pacman-based OSG software. It will fix a [[http://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/SOFTWARE-484][serious security flaw in Tomcat 5.5]] and it will fix [[http://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/SOFTWARE-485][a problem with the Gratia PBS probe]].

---++ Status Reports

---+++ Doug
   * !DocFest Monday and Tuesday and worked on Storage Element documentation
   * Bestman2 dependencies and build procedures:
   * New bestman2 does not package dependencies
   * Also Re-building bestman2 with new changes Neha introduced.

---+++ Mat
   * Upgrading GUMS to the 1.4 prerelease.
   * Figuring out how Koji ACLs work.
   * Setting up an SL6 build host for koji.

---+++ Maxim
   * !uberFTP test added to test_12, testing is done for up- and download, one thread and then 10 parallel threads, in the latter case the temporary test file generated by 'dd' to get a decent size, as opposed to the tiny one that comes with the distribution.
   * investigating the setup of glexec in order to configure it to use grid-mapfile, work in progress (a stub for test_40 created). The test will be pretty basic e.g. switching from the root identity to vdttest.

---+++ Neha
   * finished functionality validation of bestman2.2.0-6. all tests were successful. https://gw014k0.fnal.gov:8443/validation_tests/
   * resolved my first bestman bug/feature-addition - https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/SOFTWARE-482
   * investigated and found root cause of problem http://jira.opensciencegrid.org/browse/SOFTWARE-451

---+++ Scot
   * ported the VDT Cleanup Scripts.
   * did some RSV work and support, including beginning work on making RSV and Condor-Cron work with non-standard Condor locations

---+++ Suchandra

Software development:
