---+++ Tim
Last week, I worked only 2 days due to illness, and then some of that time was spent on non-OSG tasks.

In any case, I got Condor 7.6.4 rebuilt (to fix its revision string) and into the testing repository.  I am waiting for Condor 7.6.6 to be tagged (hopefully today), and then I will turn the crank on a new release.

I am about ready to start work on the next significant updates to the osg-test software.  There is [[TestingPlans][a TWiki page for the work]] (and associated design ideas):

On a related note, I have been answering a few questions from Maxim about his work on writing UberFTP and gLExec tests.